TITLE: Complete Authorizer Example
DESCRIPTION: Full example showing Authorizer client initialization and usage with identity context, policy context, and resource context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/aserto-dev/aserto-docs/blob/main/docs/software-development-kits/javascript/express.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {
  Authorizer,
  identityContext,
  policyContext,
  policyInstance,
} from "@aserto/aserto-node";

const authClient = new Authorizer(
  {
    authorizerServiceUrl: "localhost:8282",
    caFile: `${process.env.HOME}/.local/share/topaz/certs/grpc-ca.crt`
  },
);

authClient
  .Is({
    identityContext: identityContext(
      "rick@the-citadel.com",
      "SUB"
    ),
    policyInstance: policyInstance("rebac", "rebac"),
    policyContext: policyContext("rebac.check", ["allowed"]),
    resourceContext: {
      object_type: "group",
      object_id: "evil_genius",
      relation: "member",
    },
  })
```

